Durban - Eleven passengers were left injured after a minibus taxi rolled in Ireland Street in Verulam on Monday. Nick Dollman, Netcare 911 media liaison said Netcare 911 responded to reports of a serious crash in Verulam before 7am. “Paramedics from Netcare 911 and other private ambulance services attended to eleven patients at the scene, two had sustained serious injuries with the others sustaining injuries that ranged from relatively minor to moderate. Netcare 911 has transported three patients from the scene including one of the seriously injured passengers. He is a thirty seven year old man and was attended to by a Netcare 911 Advanced Life Support Paramedic and analgesic medication was administered to control his pain,” said Dollman. The injured passengers alleged that the minibus taxi was unable to negotiate the curve near the corner of Ireland and Todd Streets and crashed down an embankment and rolled before coming to a stop in the car park of a local shop, said Dollman. The fire department and police were at the scene and will be investigating. Daily News